gov.va.med.srcalc.vista.vistalink

Class VistaLinkProcedureCaller

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.srcalc.vista.vistalink.VistaLinkProcedureCaller
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    VistaProcedureCaller

    public final class VistaLinkProcedureCaller
extends java.lang.Object
implements VistaProcedureCaller

    Provides a simple interface to call VistA Remote Procedures. Uses VistALink.

    Per Effective Java Item 17, this class is marked final because it was not designed for inheritance.

      • doRpc

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> doRpc(gov.va.med.vistalink.adapter.cci.VistaLinkConnectionSpec connectionSpec,
                                     RemoteProcedure procedure,
                                     java.lang.String... args)
                                       throws org.springframework.dao.DataAccessException,
                                              javax.security.auth.login.FailedLoginException,
                                              javax.security.auth.login.AccountNotFoundException,
                                              javax.security.auth.login.LoginException

        Like doRpc(String, RemoteProcedure, String...), but supports any VistaLinkConnectionSpec. Intended to facilitate authentication via different methods.

        Note that the thrown Exceptions are more specific than for other methods to facilitate authentication failure reporting.

        Throws:
        javax.security.auth.login.FailedLoginException - if the give ConnectionSpec specified an access/verify code pair but it was not correct
        javax.security.auth.login.AccountNotFoundException - if the given ConnectionSpec specified a user identifier (e.g., DUZ) that could not be matched to a VistA user
        javax.security.auth.login.LoginException - if unable to re-authenticate using the given ConnectionSpec for any other reason
        org.springframework.dao.DataAccessException - if an error occurs in communicating with VistA
